To create a `MutationObserver` that watches for dynamically added child elements and logs their tag names, you can use the following code:

```javascript
// Create a new MutationObserver instance
const observer = new MutationObserver((mutationsList, observer) => {
  // Iterate over each mutation record
  mutationsList.forEach(mutation => {
    // Check if the mutation type is 'childList'
    if (mutation.type === 'childList') {
      // Iterate over each added node
      mutation.addedNodes.forEach(node => {
        // Check if the node is an element
